---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Method | FrontierGraph"
  description="How FrontierGraph turns the economics literature graph into deterministic ranked research opportunities."
>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <span class="eyebrow">Method note</span>
      <h1>How FrontierGraph works</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        The system is built around one hard constraint: AI may help convert text into graph structure, but the ranking
        itself should remain deterministic, inspectable, and open to scrutiny.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <span class="eyebrow">1</span>
          <h3>Build the graph</h3>
          <p class="card-copy">
            Papers become directed claim edges between coded economics concepts. This is the only stage where AI is
            allowed.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <span class="eyebrow">2</span>
          <h3>Score missing links</h3>
          <p class="card-copy">
            The engine combines gap signals, path support, motif completion, hub penalties, field distance, and prior contact.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <span class="eyebrow">3</span>
          <h3>Inspect the evidence</h3>
          <p class="card-copy">
            Users move from a shortlist to mediators, paths, supporting papers, and exportable idea briefs.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section split-grid">
      <article class="content-panel">
        <span class="eyebrow">What drives the ranking</span>
        <h2>Signals</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">
          Underexplored concept-pair gaps, path-implied missing direct edges, motif completion, low prior contact, field
          distance, and hub penalties.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="content-panel">
        <span class="eyebrow">What the beta is not doing</span>
        <h2>Current scope</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">
          No user accounts, no saved agendas, no downstream impact forecasting, and no custom frontend beyond Streamlit yet.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="content-panel">
        <span class="eyebrow">Stance</span>
        <h2>Tool, not oracle</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">
          FrontierGraph is designed to assist judgment, not replace it. It surfaces structured opportunities and exposes the evidence.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
